d leaf applications and perspectival modes of representation complement each other. Therefore, this book revises the history of perspective and gives answers to the question of how the gold ground became a blind spot in art historical research over the past decades.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aGoldgrund. 4aItalien. 4aMittelalter. 4aPerspektive. 4aReligion. 4aRenaissance. 4aTafelmalerei. 4aWissenschaftsgeschichte. 7aART / History / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aGold ground, perspective, renaissance, medieval art.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cprintz978342298938240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783422800533zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783422800533zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783422800533/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA